definitions.definition: A country in Southeast Asia . Official name: Republic of the Union of Myanmar . Capital: Naypyidaw . Also known as Burma (which was formerly the official name).
The Sino-Tibetan official language of the country of Myanmar.
The script in which the Myanmar language is written.
